# Ethical Approach

#### When learning about AI, it is crucial to integrate discussions on ethics due to the profound societal impacts and ethical dilemmas the technology presents. This curriculum weaves ethical considerations throughout, rather than relegating ethics to a single lesson.

#### By embedding ethical discussions, case studies, and extension opportunities into the learning experience, students gain a deeper, more nuanced understanding of AIâ€™s implications, encouraging critical thinking and responsible innovation.

## Leaders Framework 


#### LEADERS is an acronym representing key principles designed to guide lessons and discussions about the societal impacts of AI, including bias and ethical concerns. These principles provide reflective practices to help educators better prepare for these important conversations.

